caption: Rosded has the best Thai food! Their ingredients are fresh and each dish is made with love. The flavors are vibrant and well balanced. I love their Pad Thai & Shrimp Fried Rice. Only Thai place I will go to from now.
I just wanted to know where this place was. It's in walking distance to the Brown Line the Western Ave Stop. And it was the place, never been inside here. My sister has. Maybe I might stop in.

Boy haven't been here for awhile ( probably 4-5 yrs ) i order two entrees. Ordered extra shrimp on one and ask to omit couple ingredients in second. Of course upon receiving my order ( take out ) both are wrong,  instead of extra shrimp they add chicken and the second entree they never removed peppers and carrots as i requested. Place was quiet during early weekday so it wasn't busy. really disappointed in the quality too Place used to be good 10 yrs ago or so. Must be new ownership would love to support small business but when something like this happens it's hard to return when there literally 6-8 thai restaurants within 1 mile radius.

Might well be best Thai restaurant in the city or burbs. If not, one of the best. Quality and delicious recipes are what make this worth thr trip everytime. Panang is awesome as is the fried chicken. Soups also are killer, esp Tom Yum. Prices are very low for quality and quantity you receive. Been going here for over 35 years and never been disappointed.
Stopped for a quick Thai tea and it was DELICIOUS!!
Generous portions and great service for both carry out and dine in.

Rosded is great! In a neighborhood that has no shortage of Thai restaurants, this place stands out for it's tasty food. When I'm looking for a quaint place for a cheap date night or a quick take out meal, this is my Thai restaurant of choice.
Super cozy environment and good warm noodles or curry for a winter day. The staff was very friendly.
Great place to go. If you have not tried this restaurant, I highly recommend.
Cozy.

I used to like this restaurant ,  small good taste and good services ... ❌ Now it is bad .. ❌ VERY BAD ❌ .. This place change new people in the kitchen all the time. Now new owner made is worst. Food is bad 😢  Served sour mango  😢 Mango must be sweet to have with sticky rice I just have 2 spoons and tell the owner she taste it and agree it is bad ..... But I still have to pay for it ❌ 😡 ❌ Bye Bye Forever 🔷 So many good Thai Restaurants near by 🔷
Excellent food and service

Service was a bit slow, but server was pleasant... food was the best I've had in Lincoln Square excellent satay, and good tom kha but the larb salad has way too much overpowering mint and  its too dry. More lime juice, more cilantro, less mint would perfect it. Overall, I would go back and try it again.
Super Pad Thai! Didn’t disappoint.
It never disappoints, always good.
Great.
Crispy catfish with sweet chili are a must dish to order. Has not failed me yet since 1988...

caption: New Thai place in the area, which is saying a lot because there are many great ones. Food and service are top notch.

Good Thai home cooking with authentic flavors. We were introduced by our Thai friends and were amazed by the flavors. Try the different curries and the appetizers. Expect quick no frills service, street parking and public parking lot are both available.

This place is hard to find unless you're looking, but what a gem! I can't speak on how traditional the food is (I'm white) but it is well priced, delicious, and the portions never leave me hungry. I order the Crazy Noodle (Pad Kee Mao) and it's supposed to come spicy but it doesn't really, so this is a wonderful dish for newbies to try and you can always add spice to taste with the sauces they have on every table. The place is nice and quiet when I visit on my lunch break and the staff is always super nice and attentive.
Small little place with some great tasting dishes..

My wife and I had been wanting to try this place since we stumbled across it a few months ago and it didn't let us down. Both of our meals were very good and you couldn't beat the price. I recommend if you are in the mood for Thai!
Great Thai food, great portions, great prices
Hands down my favorite Thai restaurant in Chicago. The pineapple curry with pork and tofu is my go to. Pair it with their Thai crispy rolls and BBQ pork won ton soup, and you'll be in heaven.
Perhaps one of the best Thai food restaurants in Chicago and it's a small hidden little gem so the prices are extremely affordable and the service is excellent.

I have been dining at this authentic little storefront Thai restaurant since the early 1980s, and it is still my favorite. The heat has been toned down some since then, but they will make it spicy if you ask. Their Pad Thai is the standard by which I judge all others, and the Rosded soup just can't be beat. And to top it off, it is SO inexpensive.
Quite authentic and very delicious
Great casual place for authentic Thai food. I had the red curry with pineapple and shrimps and it was delicious. Will definitely come again.
Very good food
Great little Thai restaurant near the Old Town School of Folk Music.
Found this small cozy place by accident. The food excellent. Authentic Thai flavors. Clean and good service. Great for families.
gang panang nuer pi porn
Authentic and simple Thai food. Better than most.
This little restaurant is one of my favorite in the area. Delicious food at affordable prices.
Pretty meh, to be honest. Food lacked flavor, service was slow.
long list of food options
(Translated by Google) It is my favorite food and I have been a customer for 22 years. Excellent meal.  (Original) Es mi comida preferida y soy cliente por 22 años. Excelente comida.
BEST Thai Restaurant in the city PERIOD!

The food Is good, great taste, However: I had my family there to celebrate a birthday Saturday march 18th  , 7 people, it seem to be an inconvenience to put two tables side by side to make it a single group, the lady place them quick and uneven(no exaggeration), we only got 5 menus, we were ready to order and no order was taken for a while(we were the only customer at the time!) we place the menus one on top of the other to make it Obvious and made no difference, the lady was right next to us talking to the delivery guy for ever, the driver in a seat just chatting with this lady, We were never offered more water than the one glass that was first served,  They seem kind of annoyed that we came, it was 8:20 pm, 40 minutes before they closed, when we order two extra dishes we were asked if they were "to go", I was shocked by the service since it had so many good reviews but this is the first and last visit for me. we spent :$108.00 with a $20.00 tip, I never short-tip people but for that I feel that I'm at least entitled to an Honest review.
This is the best Thai in Lincoln Square.
Amazing small home style Thai restaurant

No frills family run business since 1976. Focus on great Thai food made with fresh ingredients and homemade sauces. Curries and Rosded Supreme are excellent and economically priced. Seating is simple, institutional tables and chairs but that's overcome by friendly hosts.
Best Thai restaurant in Chicago. Great menu, great prices, great flavor. Open daily.
Great  food at great price
Excellent food with a more interesting menu than the usual Chicago Thai joint, with super friendly service.

Loved this place until the nice man who was the waiter there forever retired and moved back to Thailand. Now they have two ladies there that are just rude. The older one ignores me and the young one is clearly enamored with my husband. On Mother's Day I twice told her I wanted Spicy Thai Basil with ground beef. She brought out an Americanized version assuming I didn't know what I wanted. My husband clarified, in Thai, what I wanted and she much later brought out something with zero spice. ZERO! I had ordered a Thai iced tea and only after she didn't bring it with the other drinks and my husband asked her where it was did she say that they were out. She twice refilled all the water on the table except mine. We're giving it one more shot but I have experienced bigotry before, having had the nerve to be white and marry a Thai man, but these ladies need to get their acts together or they will ruin a once great restaurant!
I'm Thai and I come here when I'm craving home cooked traditional food! It's not cooked for the American palate. If you like hot, spicy  real Thai food come to this place!!!
This is my favorite thai place in the city, try the Rama Chicken.
What a great place! BYOB is always a win. 20 of us went for dinner and ended up with a bill that only cost us around $10 each. Crazy affordable, and crazy delicious.

Authentic and true to the core Thai food that differentiate northern from southern cuisine. Not your typical Americanized Thai food. The place is small but very intimate with authentic thai dining experience.
Owner always remembers what we order. Food is great and service is awesome.
